==========================================================
PURPOSE
==========================================================

This document defines the official development workflow for the NEXOTFE project.

Every AI engineer must follow this workflow.

Its objective is to maximize productivity, reduce rework, preserve architecture consistency and optimize development time.

==========================================================
GENERAL PRINCIPLE
==========================================================

The project is developed one module at a time.

Never work on multiple business modules simultaneously.

Complete one module before starting another.

==========================================================
MODULE LIFE CYCLE
==========================================================

Every module follows the same sequence.

1. Business Analysis

Understand the approved business process.

Confirm that the business rules already exist.

If a business rule is missing, ask the project owner.

Never invent business rules.

==========================================================
2. Database Review
==========================================================

Compare the approved business rules with the current Supabase structure.

Identify only real differences.

Never redesign approved structures.

==========================================================
3. Approval
==========================================================

If database modifications are required,

request approval before changing Supabase.

Never modify the database without authorization.

==========================================================
4. Implementation
==========================================================

After approval:

Implement database changes.

Generate migrations.

Update backend.

Update frontend.

Remove mock data.

Connect the module to Supabase.

==========================================================
5. Testing
==========================================================

Verify:

Create

Read

Update

Logical Delete (if applicable)

Relationships

Validation

Business rules

==========================================================
6. Freeze
==========================================================

When the module is approved:

Freeze it.

Avoid new improvements unless:

A bug exists.

A business rule changes.

The project owner explicitly requests an enhancement.

==========================================================
CURRENT DEVELOPMENT PRIORITY
==========================================================

Development priority is defined by business value.

Current order:

1. Master Data

2. Commercial Modules

3. Engineering

4. Purchasing

5. Planning

6. Production

7. Advanced Modules

Never change this order without approval.

==========================================================
IMPLEMENTATION RULES
==========================================================

Always preserve:

Business consistency.

Existing data.

Approved architecture.

Approved naming.

Approved standards.

Never create temporary solutions.

==========================================================
FRONT-END WORKFLOW
==========================================================

When refining a page:

Do not redesign.

Refine.

Standardize.

Balance layouts.

Improve usability.

Maintain visual consistency.

==========================================================
BACK-END WORKFLOW
==========================================================

When working on Supabase:

Protect existing data.

Use migrations.

Maintain RLS.

Maintain audit fields.

Maintain multi-company support.

Never implement shortcuts.

==========================================================
COMMUNICATION
==========================================================

Avoid long reports.

Avoid unnecessary explanations.

After completing a task, report only:

Files modified.

Database objects modified.

Migration created.

Manual verification required.

==========================================================
PROJECT PHILOSOPHY
==========================================================

Progress is measured by completed modules.

Not by lines of code.

Not by documentation.

Not by reports.

A completed, tested and approved module is the unit of progress.

==========================================================
FINAL PRINCIPLE
==========================================================

Every engineering effort must generate practical value.

Time, budget and engineering resources are valuable.

Avoid unnecessary work.

Avoid unnecessary discussions.

Focus on delivering finished modules with professional quality.